  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "To clear your Hotmail inbox (now part of Outlook.com), you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Access Your Account\n- Go to the Outlook.com website and sign in with your Hotmail account credentials.\n\n### 2. Navigate to Your Inbox\n- Once logged in, you'll be directed to your inbox where you can see all your emails.\n\n### 3. Select Emails to Delete\n- **Single Email**: Click on the email you want to delete to select it.\n- **Multiple Emails**: To select multiple emails, check the box next to each email you wish to delete. You can also select all emails on the current page by clicking the checkbox at the top.\n\n### 4. Delete Emails\n- After selecting the emails, look for the trash bin icon (\ud83d\uddd1\ufe0f) at the top of the inbox. Click on this icon to delete the selected emails.\n\n### 5. Empty Deleted Items Folder\n- Deleted emails go to the \"Deleted Items\" folder. To permanently delete them:\n  - Navigate to the \"Deleted Items\" folder on the left side.\n  - You can either select all emails and delete them again or right-click on the \"Deleted Items\" folder and select \"Empty folder.\"\n\n### 6. Use the Sweep Feature (Optional)\n- If you want to delete all emails from a specific sender or delete old emails in bulk:\n  - Go to your inbox and find an email from the sender.\n  - Click on that email to open it.\n  - On the top menu, select \u201cSweep\u201d and choose the deletion option you prefer (e.g., delete all from the sender, keep only the latest message, etc.).\n\n### 7. Organize with Folders (Optional)\n- If you don\u2019t want to delete everything, consider creating folders to organize your emails. You can move emails to various folders instead of deleting them.\n\n### 8. Check Storage (Optional)\n- If you're trying to clear space, keep in mind that Hotmail/Outlook accounts have a storage limit. You might want to periodically check your storage and manage other folders (e.g., Sent Items, Spam).\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to manage and clear your Hotmail inbox effectively!",
